Metadata: Metabolites of the sponge "Strongylophora durissima" from Maricaban Island, Philippines

The sponge "Strongylophora durissima" from the Philippines contains the known meroditerpenoid​s strongylophorin​e-​2 and strongylophorin​e-​3, three new meroditerpenoid​s, strongylophorin​es-​4, -5, and -8, and two novel enediones, strongylophorin​e-​6 and strongylophorin​e-​7. The structures of the new strongylophorin​es 4-8 were elucidated by interpretation of spectral data and chemical interconversion​s. The strongylophorin​es show mild activity against Gram-positive bacteria.
